  "texts": [
    "Should that be an argument against disclosure, a small random sample of the minimal cells would suffice to estimate the presence of large biases in the modeling framework.",
    "The way out of the manipulation objection is explicability.",
    "We propose three novel disclosure standards to aid with improving the transparency of AI polling.",
    "It is our view that AI pollsters should disclose (i) details on ML algorithms used for weighting and prediction models; (ii) variable importance metrics for each model fit as part of the estimation procedure; (iii) predictions on benchmark cells to ascertain relative bias.",
    "We believe these standards are sufficient to establish the quality of a given AI pollster's estimation procedure, and protect against malicious actors making extraordinary or motivated claims."
